<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Homage" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Homage,</orth> 1) fealty and service professed to a superior lord: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.124" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 124</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.225" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 225</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.204" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 204</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.7.31" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 7, 31</bibl>. <cit><quote>pays h. to us,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 4.3.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 3, 64</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to do h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.113" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 113</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.1.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 1, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 2, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.6.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 6, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 2, 28</bibl>. <cit><quote>do themselves h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 1, 54</bibl></cit> (know no masters but themselves).<lb />2) respect, obeisance, reverence: <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.267" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 267</bibl>. <cit><quote>to do h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.104" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 104</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.224" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 224</bibl>. <cit><quote>to do h. to:</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 7.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 7, 3</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.135" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 1, 135.</bibl> <cit><quote>to owe h. to:</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 43</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>